com.conceptwave.scripting
Class ValidationErrorList

com.conceptwave.scripting.Object
  com.conceptwave.scripting.CWScriptable
      com.conceptwave.scripting.ValidationErrorList

public class ValidationErrorList
extends CWScriptable

List of run-time validation error messages. The maximum number of errors are specified at construction time. Can be created with zero errors count in which case will not store any error messages but will keep flag to show if any error has been given to the list.

addErrorMessage

public com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean addErrorMessage(CwObject dObj,
                                                         String leafPath,
                                                         String msgCode,
                                                         com.conceptwave.scripting.Object severity,
                                                         com.conceptwave.scripting.Object inserts,
                                                         String varPath)
Add error message to the error list

Parameters:
dObj - Validated data object (the culprit of the message). If null or undefined, then it takes the current validated object as culprit.
Current validated object is being set automatically when validate() or validateEx() method is called for the data object. If the current object is not defined, it still adds the error to the list. Errors without culprits are displayed at the form header as model errors.
leafPath - Name of the target leaf. If the leaf is null of undefined, the error is added at the object level.
NOTE: The leaf should be the direct leaf of dObj.
To add an error to the inner data structure container, pass the container instance as "dObj" and specify instance's variable path as "varPath" parameter.
The path should be related to the current validated object.
msgCode - The error code or a string message
severity - Optional: Severity of the error: 'e'|"error", 'w'|"warn"|"warning", 'i'|"info"|"information". If null or not specified, it sets "error" severity. Case insensitive.
inserts - Optional: Parameters for the error message.
varPath - Optional: Variable path of the specified dObj according to the current validated object.
Returns:
true if the error list is full
Throws:
java.lang.Exception - "DE0262" if the leaf is specified but not found or data object cannot be obtained
